{{Quote|On Stensen's Colony there are Ghothian slime pools which display a greater degree of intelligence than you did when you initiated this project.|Hyndis Kogler's message to Doctor Tobias|<ref name="IS2">[[Imperial Sourcebook (Second Edition)|''Imperial Sourcebook'', Second Edition]]</ref>}}
A '''Ghothian slime pool''' was a natural formation that hailed from the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories']] [[Ghothia system/Legends|Ghothia system]]. In a message sent by the [[Time/Legends|time]] shortly after the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], [[Imperial Intelligence/Legends|Imperial Intelligence]] [[Imperial officer/Legends|officer]] [[Hyndis Kogler]], who was highly displeased with an initiative undertaken by their Intelligence colleague [[Doctor/Legends|Doctor]] [[Tobias]], compared unfavorably the latter's intelligence, as displayed by the initiative, to that of some Ghothian [[Slime/Legends|slime]] pools on the celestial body [[Stensen's Colony]].

==Description==
A Ghothian slime pool was a [[Slime/Legends|slime]]-related natural formation<ref name="IS2" /> that originated in<ref name="Planetnamia">{{Planetnamia|other=Ghothian [[Slime/Legends|slime]] pools|system=[[Ghothia system/Legends|Ghothia system]]|legends=1}}</ref> the [[Ghothia system/Legends|Ghothia system]] of the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories']] [[Stensen sector/Legends|Stensen sector]].<ref name="EAOC">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-atlas-online-companion|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion|int=Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion}}</ref> Ghothian slime pools could be found on [[Stensen's Colony]], a celestial body<ref name="IS2" /> in the Stensen [[Sector/Legends|sector's]] [[Stensen's Colony system/Legends|Stensen's Colony system]].<ref name="EAOC" />

==History==
At some point by the [[Time/Legends|time]] shortly after the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], [[Hyndis Kogler]], an [[Imperial officer/Legends|officer]] of the [[Infiltration]] branch of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] [[Imperial Intelligence/Legends|Intelligence]] service, sent a message to [[Doctor/Legends|Doctor]] [[Tobias]], a member of the service's [[Tech (Imperial Intelligence)|Tech]] branch. Kogler was extremely upset with Tobias' ill-considered plan of sending out several modified [[3PO-series protocol droid/Legends|3PO-series protocol droids]] in an attempt to infiltrate [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] facilities, and in the message the [[Officer/Legends|officer]] claimed that some Ghothian slime pools on Stensen's Colony exhibited a "greater degree of intelligence" than Tobias did when coming up with the idea. Imperial Intelligence later included the message in a report prepared for an Imperial [[Grand Moff/Legends|Grand Moff]], which in turn was added by Alliance [[Historian/Legends|historian]] [[Major/Legends|Major]] [[Arhul Hextrophon/Legends|Arhul Hextrophon]] to a compilation of Imperial documents for Alliance [[Supreme Commander (Alliance)/Legends|Supreme Commander]] [[Mon Mothma/Legends|Mon Mothma]] and other Rebel officers.<ref name="IS2" />

==Behind the scenes==
Ghothian slime pools&mdash;spelled as "Ghothian Slime pools"&mdash;were first mentioned in the [[1989]] ''[[Imperial Sourcebook]]'', written by [[Greg Gorden]] for [[West End Games]]' ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]''.<ref name="ISB">''[[Imperial Sourcebook]]''</ref> Their name was subsequently spelled as "Ghothian slime pools" in the [[1994]] [[Imperial Sourcebook (Second Edition)|Second Edition]] of the book.<ref name="IS2" />

